<assessment id="_u1_m1_vital_function_inline05">
    <title>Control and Regulation</title>
    <page>
        <question id="_u01_m01_vital05_1">
            <body>What is the most important regulator of function in the body?</body>
            <multiple_choice shuffle="true" id="ans">
                <choice value="heart">heart</choice>
                <choice value="bones">bones</choice>
                <choice value="eyes">eyes</choice>
                <choice value="stomach">stomach</choice>
                <choice value="brain">brain</choice>
            </multiple_choice>
            <part>
                <response match="heart" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. The heart is important for transporting nutrients needed in a variety of processes but does not regulate functions within the body. The brain controls the heartbeat.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="bones" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. Bones do not regulate body functions. </feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="eyes" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. Eyes help us
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194422-0400"?><?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194435-0400" comment="Change OK?"?>interact<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194420-0400" content="integrate"?><?oxy_comment_end?>
                        with the environment but we use the brain to process information both
                        consciously (by making decisions) and unconsciously (with automated
                        processes).</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="stomach" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. The stomach is an important part of the digestive system
                        but does not regulate
                        function<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194457-0400"?>s<?oxy_insert_end?>.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="brain" score="1">
                    <feedback>Correct. We use the brain to process information and control bodily functions both consciously (by making decisions) and unconsciously (by controlling heartbeat).</feedback>
                </response>
                <hint>We
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194742-0400"?>either<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194741-0400" content="both"?>
                    consciously
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194747-0400"?>or<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194746-0400" content="and"?>
                    unconsciou<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20111029T194527-0400"?>s<?oxy_insert_end?>ly
                    control most of our body functions with this organ.</hint>
            </part>
        </question>

